<TITLE> Bomb found near Banani Puja pavilion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 25 (bdnews24.com)--RAB on Friday night recovered a bomb from a playground near a Puja pavilion in Banani in Dhaka, spreading panic among Hindu devotees celebrating Durga Puja. Additional director general colonel Mizanur Rahman told bdnews24.com that they found the bomb at 8:15pm, kept in a tubular can of Pringles potato chips beside a wall outside the pavilion "On a tip-off that somebody was carrying bombs at the Puja pavilion, we came and recovered the bomb." "Area near the bomb has been sealed. Work is on to defuse it." The bomb might have been kept to spread panic, he said. He added that people in the pavilion had been evacuated safely. "RAB's bomb disposal unit has taken the bomb to examine it. People could have been injured if it was detonated." RAB personnel and sniffer dogs started searching the playground at around 10pm, Rahman added. bd
